  "_comment": [
    "Pinned controller source for every constant in CONST. check_constants.py verifies each",
    "named key and value against these commits and FAILS the build on any mismatch, missing",
    "constant, or unavailable source.",
    "",
    "The controller changed DURING the deployment, so a single commit does not describe it.",
    "Data collection ran 2026-06-15 to 2026-06-29:",
    "  * b84e2f8 (2026-06-15 14:37) ran the first session days;",
    "  * be46774 ('STABLE VERSION', 2026-06-18 16:30) ran from 18 June to the end.",
    "  * No commits landed between 2026-06-18 and 2026-07-05.",
    "",
    "Every constant this analysis depends on is IDENTICAL across both commits — the 18 June",
    "changes touched proactive-messaging logic, prompt text and a greeted-entry pruning routine,",
    "not thresholds, meal sizes, energy costs or the affinity EMA. The checker therefore verifies",
    "BOTH commits and additionally asserts they agree with each other, so the analysis rests on a",
    "constant that was stable for the whole deployment rather than on one snapshot of it.",
    "",
    "`commit` is the reference (end-of-deployment) commit; `deployment_commits` is the full set",
    "that must agree."
  ],
